needs translation and incorporation into article|date=January 2018}} '''Feicheng''' ({{zh|c=肥城 |p=Féichéng}}) is a [[county-level city]] under the administration of [[Tai'an]] City in the west of [[Shandong]] province, China. {{Asof|2017}}, the population was 992,000.<ref name="official intro">{{Cite web|url=http://www.feicheng.gov.cn/about/contents/124/54572.html |script-title=zh:肥城市情概况 |publisher=Feicheng People's Government |date=18 September 2017 |access-date=2018-05-04}}</ref> Part of the [[Great Wall of Qi]] starts here, and is listed on the People's Republic of China's list of cultural artifacts.
Billionaire businessman [[Xiao Jianhua]] grew up in Feicheng.<ref name="nytimeswithchoiceattiananmen">{{cite news|last1=Barboza|first1=David|last2=Forsythe|first2=Michael|title=With Choice at Tiananmen, Student Took Road to Riches|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2014/06/04/world/asia/tiananmen-era-students-different-path-to-power-in-china.html?action=click&contentCollection=Asia%20Pacific&module=RelatedCoverage&region=EndOfArticle&pgtype=article&_r=0|accessdate=February 1, 2017|work=The New York Times|date=June 3, 2014|quote=He grew up in Feicheng, a poor farming village in a mountainous region of the eastern Chinese province of Shandong, one of six children born to a middle school teacher and his wife.}}</ref>
